  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is difference between Authorisation and Authentication?",
  "response": "Authentication and Authorization are related but distinct concepts in security and access control:\n\nAuthentication:\n1. Verifies \"Who you are\"\n2. Confirms user's identity\n3. Validates credentials (username/password)\n4. Occurs before authorization\n5. Answers the question: \"Are you who you claim to be?\"\n6. Examples:\n- Login process\n- Checking ID\n- Biometric verification\n- Password validation\n\nAuthorization:\n1. Determines \"What you can do\"\n2. Grants/restricts access to specific resources\n3. Defines user permissions and privileges\n4. Occurs after authentication\n5. Answers the question: \"Are you allowed to access this resource?\"\n6. Examples:\n- Admin vs. regular user access\n- Read/write permissions\n- Role-based access control\n- Specific system capabilities\n\nKey Differences:\n- Authentication identifies users\n- Authorization defines user rights\n- Authentication comes first\n- Authorization depends on authentication\n- Authentication validates credentials\n- Authorization manages access levels\n\nAnalogy:\n- Authentication = Showing passport at airport\n- Authorization = Determining which areas you can enter based on ticket/clearance",
  "temperature": 1.0,
